  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> @Jerskouille what happens on a UX side if the url hPP is different from the state.hitsPerPage one and not in the provided options?\n\nIt currently throwed, with this PR it will use it and display an empty option. \n\n> If we could just say \"let's use the one from the developer\" and move on that would be awesome, I really wonder if we even need to warn..\n\nOne argument against this is that we call the `init` after the `getConfiguration`s and setting a config after all the `getConfiguration`s doesn't seem that coherent. But why not if you think that's not an issue.\n\n> We need to move forward on that because right now the documentation is broken because of an unsupported undefined option. What are the next steps @Jerskouille ?\n\nNow that I used `window.console`, I think this is mergeable. Let's see if we want to improve this afterwards with @vvo 's suggestion or something like it?\n",
